track.name: Hoodoo Man Blues
comments: Very unusual overall sound for this cut. The guitar is interesting, the whole track is sweet!

PattySauce, Well, it's weird, there's still some good music out there, but it seems these days like you have to really dig for it, whereas in the past it was right out in the open! By the way what is Patty Sauce? Sounds like something that you put on hamburgers (just kidding)!
Today's music does nothing to me!!! But when I hear this I can't help but smile and dance!!! The Blues rock!!!!
fuckin awesome track.  his stuff with buddy guy, first super group.  youuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuu x
" somebody done whoodooed the whoodoo man."
So good I can't stand it.
Might just be the first guitar player that played his guitar through a Leslie!

é o cara!
tem outros também, claro.... não precisa nem citar!
You gotta love this track if you dig blues. I love when he does that Oooooooooow and starts playing a harp solo.
blow on junior, that hoodoo will make you strange things, yes yes it it will

The least technically gifted of the great harp players but he made up for it in front.  You gotta love the early Guy/Wells stuff.  This could be Wells' best performance.  Just listen to how that band grooves.
